The paper proposes a new entity linking model based on BERT and contextualized word embeddings. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically entity linking (EL), which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the model uses machine learning techniques such as joint training of mention detection and entity disambiguation, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its model on several standard EL datasets, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of contextualized word embeddings suggests that it could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
